        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 5:27AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 527 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northwest of Durham to New Mobeetie to
17 miles north of Skellytown. Movement was southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shamrock, New Mobeetie, Higgins, Canadian, Twitty, Allison, Lela,
Lefors, Lake Marvin, Kellerville, Miami, Lora, Mobeetie, Pampa,
Wheeler, Codman, and Briscoe.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 156 and 176.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
